From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dimitris Panokostas <midwan@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 15:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] uae: implement and export ppc_cpu_flush_jit

AmigaOS 3.x / WarpOS drives the PPC as a coprocessor: the m68k loads and
patches PPC code/data directly in shared RAM. Those writes bypass QEMU's PPC
softmmu, so the PPC keeps executing stale translation blocks and the early
m68k<->PPC handshake deadlocks (BlitterStudio/amiberry#2114). UAE calls
ppc_cpu_flush_jit() from uae_ppc_execute_check()/quick() to invalidate the TB
cache; the old qemu-uae plugin exported it but the QEMU 11 port dropped it,
so the call became a no-op. Reinstate it (queued cross-thread tb flush) and
export it from the plugin. UAE gates the call on the m68k being the active
CPU, so it does not retranslate during OS4 PPC-only execution.
---
 uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c       | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 uae/qemu-uae-ld64.symbols |  1 +
 uae/qemu-uae.symbols      |  1 +
 3 files changed, 18 insertions(+)

--- a/uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c
@@ -388,6 +388,25 @@
     }
 }
 
+/*
+ * Flush the PPC translation block cache so the CPU re-reads code/data that the
+ * m68k modified directly in shared RAM. The m68k's writes bypass QEMU's PPC
+ * softmmu, so without this the PPC keeps executing stale translation blocks and
+ * the AmigaOS 3.x / WarpOS handshake deadlocks (issue #2114). UAE calls this
+ * from uae_ppc_execute_check()/quick() (m68k thread) only while the m68k is the
+ * active CPU (OS3 / coprocessor mode), never when it is halted and the PPC is
+ * primary (OS4), so it does not retranslate during normal PPC-only execution.
+ */
+void PPCAPI ppc_cpu_flush_jit(void)
+{
+    if (!state.cpu) {
+        return;
+    }
+    qemu_uae_lock_if_needed();
+    queue_tb_flush(CPU(state.cpu));
+    qemu_uae_unlock_if_needed();
+}
+
 static void qemu_uae_log_cpu_state(void)
 {
     int flags = 0;
--- a/uae/qemu-uae.symbols
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae.symbols
@@ -1,5 +1,6 @@
 {
   global:
+    ppc_cpu_flush_jit;
     ppc_cpu_init;
     ppc_cpu_map_memory;
     ppc_cpu_reset;
--- a/uae/qemu-uae-ld64.symbols
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae-ld64.symbols
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+_ppc_cpu_flush_jit
 _ppc_cpu_init
 _ppc_cpu_map_memory
 _ppc_cpu_reset
